<body>
	<h1>Output</h1>

	<div class="eg">
		${message}
	</div>

	The general pattern for output in Tapestry is this: the class exposes named properties (ie. public getters), eg. <code>getMessage()</code>, 
	and the template references them, eg. &#36;<code>{message}</code>.<br/><br/>

	The reference &#36;<code>{message}</code> is called an <em>expansion</em>.<br/><br/> 

